{#def variant="nav", tone="default", extra="" #}
{#
  Title-bar window-control button. Distinct from the general-purpose
  Button primitive only in geometry (window-control sizing); its colors
  are plain design tokens (``hover:bg-fill-hover`` + ``active:bg-fill-active``,
  with the foreground supplied by ``tone``). Keyboard focus shows an accent
  outline (no offset, so no white gap appears over the colored / neutral
  titlebar).

  Those tokens are re-based per-workspace by the ``.titlebar-surface`` scope
  in app.css, which derives a black/white contrast from ``--titlebar-bg`` in
  pure CSS -- so the same button reads correctly on any workspace color and on
  the neutral chrome, with no per-element foreground variable.

  Props:
    variant
      "nav"     -- left-side icon hits (sidebar / home / back / forward /
                   requests). A square icon button -- ``p-1.5`` around the icon
                   (not fixed w/h) with a slight rounded corner. Its flex
                   wrappers use ``items-center`` so it never stretches to the
                   titlebar height.
      "crumb"   -- breadcrumb text pills (the Minds home button, the
                   workspace-switcher name): ``px-1.5 py-1`` with the same
                   rounded corner.
      "control" -- right-side native window controls (min / max / close)
                   on platforms where minds draws its own frame.
                   ``w-9 h-[38px]``, square corners (matches the OS).
    tone
      "default" -- ``text-primary`` foreground (re-based per-workspace by the
                   ``.titlebar-surface`` scope in app.css).
      "muted"   -- resting/unselected state: ``text-secondary`` rising to
                   ``text-primary`` on hover. chrome.js toggles the same
                   classes to flip selection live (see applyTitlebarContext).
      "danger"  -- close-button-only red hover regardless of accent
                   (``.titlebar-btn-danger``); use on the close control
                   to mirror native Windows / Linux behavior.

  Any HTML attribute on the tag that is not declared above (id=, title=,
  aria-*, data-*) flows through via JinjaX's ``attrs`` passthrough.
#}
{%- set _variants = {
  "nav": "p-1.5 rounded-md",
  "crumb": "px-1.5 py-1 rounded-md",
  "control": "w-9 h-[38px] rounded-none",
} -%}
{%- set _tones = {
  "default": "text-primary",
  "muted": "text-secondary hover:text-primary",
  "danger": "text-primary titlebar-btn-danger",
} -%}
{%- set _btn_base = "inline-flex items-center justify-center cursor-pointer hover:bg-fill-hover active:bg-fill-active focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-accent" -%}
{%- set _cls = _btn_base ~ " " ~ _variants[variant] ~ " " ~ _tones[tone] ~ " " ~ extra -%}
<button {{ attrs.render(type="button", classes=_cls) }}>{{ content }}</button>
